**Early retirement** in India requires a significantly larger corpus than conventional retirement at 60, because your money must last 35–45 years instead of 20–25 years. At 6% inflation, ₹1 lakh monthly spending today needs ₹4.3 crore corpus to sustain for 40 years at 7% post-retirement returns. This calculator gives you the exact corpus needed for any early retirement age.
